---
name: scljet-mutate-insert
description: SclJet read-modify-rewrite — insert a new row at an explicit rowid, kept in ascending order, cross-backend
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet insert (read-modify-rewrite)

[ByteSlice, byteSliceToList, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, KeyedRow, buildKeyedDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[insertRow](std/scljet/mutate.ssc)

```scalascript
// A table with gapped rowids (10, 20, 30). Insert a new row at rowid 25 — it lands
// between 20 and 30, existing rows pass through as raw records, and every rowid is
// preserved. Reference integrity_check accepts the result; int and JS agree.
val rows = List(
  KeyedRow(10L, List(SqlInteger(10L), SqlText("ten"))),
  KeyedRow(20L, List(SqlInteger(20L), SqlText("twenty"))),
  KeyedRow(30L, List(SqlInteger(30L), SqlText("thirty"))))

buildKeyedDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(n INTEGER, v TEXT)", rows) match
  case Right(db) =>
    insertRow(db, 2, 1, 25L, List(SqlInteger(25L), SqlText("twentyfive"))) match
      case Right(newDb) => println((newDb.length / 512).toString + ":" + byteSliceToList(newDb).toString)
      case Left(message) => println("INSERT-ERROR:" + message)
  case Left(error) => println("BUILD-ERROR:" + error.message)
```
